
Knox Wagner &quot;Bulldog&quot; Ramsey (February 13, 1926 â€“ March 19, 2005) was an American football offensive lineman in the National Football League for the Chicago Cardinals, the Philadelphia Eagles, and the Washington Redskins. Ramsey also played in the All-America Football Conference for the Los Angeles Dons. He played college football at the College of William &amp; Mary and was drafted in the fifth round of the 1948 NFL Draft by the Chicago Bears.


